    "   \"source\": \"---\\n## Summary\\n\\n| Task | Dataset | Model | Metric | Query strategy | NAUC |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| Classification | make_moons | RandomForestClassifier | accuracy | Margin sampling | `nauc_al` |\\n| Regression | Gap data | BootstrapMLP | neg-MSE | Variance (num_samples=5) | `nauc_reg_al` |\\n\\n**API recap:**\\n```python\\nX_labeled, y_labeled, scores, nauc = active_learning_loop(\\n    model,\\n    X_train, y_train,   # pool to query from\\n    X_test, y_test,     # held-out evaluation set\\n    metric=\\\"accuracy\\\",  # or \\\"mse\\\", \\\"mae\\\", \\\"auc\\\", or a callable\\n    pool_size=10,       # samples queried per iteration\\n    n_iterations=15,\\n    seed=0,\\n)\\n```\\n- `metric` strings `\\\"mse\\\"` / `\\\"mae\\\"` are negated so **higher is always better**.\\n- `nauc` ∈ [0, 1]: fraction of the ideal (constant-max) area achieved on average.\\n- No `task` parameter needed — classification vs. regression is inferred from the model.\"\n",
